How to apply these terms to your new programs

If you develop a new program, and you want it to be of the greatest possible use to the public, the best way to do this is to make it free software which everyone can redistribute and change under these terms.  To do so, you should include a copy of this License in each program you distribute.  You should also make sure that everyone else who uses the program is aware that it is governed by these terms, and that they can also do these things.

Also, when you incorporate parts of other programs, developers usually find it useful to mention some of the authors of these other programs, so you can do that in the credits or in the network documentation.
